How Components Interact
1️⃣ User Interaction

User clicks a button:

Button(
    onClick = {
        viewModel.getUsers()
    }
) {
    Text("Load Users")
}

Flow:

👤 User
   │
   ▼
🎨 UI Layer
2️⃣ UI → ViewModel

UI sends request to ViewModel.

viewModel.getUsers()
🎨 UI
   │
   ▼
🧠 ViewModel

Responsibilities:

Manage UI state
Handle user actions
Call Repository
3️⃣ ViewModel → Repository
repository.getUsers()
🧠 ViewModel
      │
      ▼
📦 Repository

Repository decides:

Should data come from:
      │
      ├── 🌐 API ?
      │
      └── 💾 Room Database ?
4️⃣ Repository → API
api.getUsers()
📦 Repository
      │
      ▼
🌐 Retrofit API

Example:

interface UserApi {

    @GET("users")
    suspend fun getUsers(): List<User>
}
5️⃣ Repository → Database
userDao.getUsers()
📦 Repository
      │
      ▼
💾 Room Database

Example:

@Dao
interface UserDao {

    @Query("SELECT * FROM users")
    fun getUsers(): List<User>
}
6️⃣ Data Returns Back
💾 Database / 🌐 API
            │
            ▼
📦 Repository
            │
            ▼
🧠 ViewModel
            │
            ▼
🎨 UI Layer
            │
            ▼
👤 User
Real Notes App Architecture
📱 Notes App
│
├── 🎨 Presentation Layer
│   ├── HomeScreen
│   ├── AddNoteScreen
│   ├── NoteDetailScreen
│   └── NotesViewModel
│
├── 🧠 Business Layer
│   ├── AddNoteUseCase
│   ├── DeleteNoteUseCase
│   ├── UpdateNoteUseCase
│   └── GetNotesUseCase
│
├── 📦 Data Layer
│   ├── NotesRepository
│   ├── NotesDao
│   └── NotesDatabase
│
├── 🌐 Network Layer
│   └── Retrofit API
│
└── 🔧 Dependency Injection
    └── Hilt
Memory Trick for Interviews
👤 User
   ↓
🎨 UI
   ↓
🧠 ViewModel
   ↓
📦 Repository
   ↓
🌐 API / 💾 Database

Formula:

User → UI → ViewModel → Repository → API/Database → Repository → ViewModel → UI → User

This is the architecture used in most modern Android apps built with Jetpack Compose 
+ MVVM + Repository + Room + Retrofit + Hilt.